        "text": "# \ud83d\udfe2 HEARTBEAT_WAKEUP\nYou have been routed ONE isolated task. \n*Task ID*: EPIC-DFP\n*Module*: SYSTEM\n*Workdir*: /home/ienliven/Projects/sdlc-factory/workspace/EPIC-DFP\n*Phase*: ARCHITECTURE\n\n## PHASE CONTEXT (ARCHITECTURE)\n### spec_payload.json\n```\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"phase_completed\": \"PLANNING\",\n  \"product_spec_hash\": \"dfp-spec-v1\",\n  \"identified_modules\": [\n    \"ui-gateway\",\n    \"logic-api\",\n    \"data-store\"\n  ],\n  \"task_id\": \"EPIC-DFP\",\n  \"module_id\": \"SYSTEM\"\n}\n```\n\n### PROD_SPEC.md\n```\n# Product Specification: Dimensional Factor Pulse (DFP)\n\n## 1. Overview\nThe Dimensional Factor Pulse (DFP) is a containerized financial dashboard designed to display a performance heatmap of factor premiums for Dimensional Fund Advisors (DFA) management. It consists of a React/Vite frontend served by Nginx, a Python/uv backend API, and a PostgreSQL database.\n\n## 2. Architecture & Modules\nThe system is divided into three primary modules:\n1. **ui-gateway**: A React/Vite frontend application styled with Tailwind CSS, utilizing `@nivo/heatmap` or `apexcharts` for visualization. It is served via Nginx, which also acts as a reverse proxy to the backend API.\n2. **logic-api**: A Python backend managed by `uv`, responsible for fetching financial data via `yfinance`, calculating factor premiums, and serving the data to the frontend.\n3. **data-store**: A PostgreSQL database used to cache daily adjusted market closes.\n\n## 3. Functional Requirements\n\n### 3.1 UI Gateway (Frontend)\n- **Framework**: React/Vite (pnpm).\n- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS.\n- **Visualization**: `@nivo/heatmap` or `apexcharts` for a grid-based heatmap (X-axis: date, Y-axis: funds, Color: positive/negative premium).\n- **Controls**:\n  - Fund Selector: Dropdown for proxy pairs (US Core Equity: DFAC vs ^GSPC, Intl. Vector: DXIV vs URTH, Emerging Markets: DFAE vs EEM).\n  - Timeframe Toggle: 1D, 5D, 1M, 6M, 1Y, YTD.\n- **Metadata**: Footer displaying \"Built by SDLC-Factory\" with automated build timestamp and git hash.\n- **Testing**: Playwright included as a dev dependency for E2E testing.\n- **UX**: Descriptive metric names, interactive heatmap with clear color differentiation, legend, vertical text for narrow columns, and tooltip on hover (date, premium value, region, proxy pair).\n- **Routing**: Nginx must serve the built assets on port 80 (mapped to host 8000) and reverse proxy `/api/*` to `http://logic-api:8001/*`.\n\n### 3.2 Logic API (Backend)\n- **Framework**: Python (managed via `uv` and `pyproject.toml`).\n- **Data Fetching**: Use `yfinance` to fetch data for DFAC, ^GSPC, DXIV, URTH, DFAE, EEM.\n- **Initialization**: Seed the last 730 days of data on first boot. Must implement a polling loop (e.g., `tenacity`) to wait for the database (up to 10 attempts, 2 seconds apart) before seeding or binding the port.\n- **Calculations**: Premium = DFA Proxy Return - Benchmark Return. Calculated and stored to 4 decimal places.\n- **Endpoints**:\n  - `/health`: Verifies backend and database connectivity.\n  - Data endpoint: Accepts `fund_id` and `timeframe`, returns filtered time-series data formatted for the frontend heatmap (e.g., pre-calculated 2D array or JSON object for `@nivo/heatmap`).\n- **Port**: Binds to 8001 internally (mapped to host 8001).\n\n### 3.3 Data Store (Database)\n- **Database**: PostgreSQL.\n- **Persistence**: Docker volumes.\n- **Network**: Internal network access only (unreachable from host).\n\n## 4. Non-Functional Requirements\n- **Authentication**: None.\n- **Containerization**: All components must be Dockerized and orchestrated via `docker-compose`.\n- **Zero-Touch Provisioning**: The stack must build and run without manual intervention.\n\n```\n\n\n## SYSTEM CONTEXT\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"module_id\": \"SYSTEM\",\n  \"regression_context\": \"No active regression reported.\",\n  \"structural_context\": \"No structural boundaries found (API_CONTRACTS.md missing or module not defined).\",\n  \"semantic_context\": \"No legacy semantic snippet queries found for this module.\",\n  \"memory_insights\": \"No historic pgvector insights found for architect.\"\n}\n```\n\nThe SDLC Protocol and your Playbook are your core instructions.\nCRITICAL: If successful, your handoff JSON must strictly validate against this schema:\n```json\n{\n  \"oneOf\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"required\": [\n        \"status\",\n        \"phase_completed\",\n        \"api_contracts_hash\",\n        \"vertical_slices\"\n      ],\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"status\": {\n          \"const\": \"success\"\n        },\n        \"phase_completed\": {\n          \"const\": \"ARCHITECTURE\"\n        },\n        \"api_contracts_hash\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        \"vertical_slices\": {\n          \"type\": \"array\",\n          \"items\": {\n            \"type\": \"object\",\n            \"required\": [\n              \"module_name\",\n              \"assigned_agent\"\n            ],\n            \"properties\": {\n              \"module_name\": {\n                \"type\": \"string\"\n              },\n              \"assigned_agent\": {\n                \"type\": \"string\"\n              },\n              \"context_queries\": {\n                \"type\": \"array\",\n                \"items\": {\n                  \"type\": \"string\"\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"required\": [\n        \"status\",\n        \"phase_completed\",\n        \"rfc_file_path\"\n      ],\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"status\": {\n          \"const\": \"rfc_requested\"\n        },\n        \"phase_completed\": {\n          \"const\": \"ARCHITECTURE\"\n        },\n        \"rfc_file_path\": {\n          \"const\": \"docs/RFC.md\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\nIf you learn an architecture-critical lesson, permanently save it for your future self using the native `sdlc_store_memory` tool.\n\n\n## WORKSPACE DIRECTORY TREE\n```text\n.\n./.state\n./.state/current.json\n./dist\n./docs\n./docs/PROD_SPEC.md\n./handoff\n./handoff/RAW_REQUIREMENTS.md\n./handoff/spec_payload.json\n./issues\n./src\n./tests\n```\n",
